RedIC

Collection of three ICs to change wool colors or wool blocks of multiple blocks with redstone events.


Usage:

Place a sign on a block and write the following lines for the different ICs (first line not necessary):


TOGGLE
[RC1000]
0:0
0:1:0:1:1:1

Thrid line: Damage Value for wool color activeColor:inactiveColor.
Fourth line: OffsetX:OffsetY:OffsetZ:width:length:height.


COPY
[RC1001]
0:1:0:1:1:1
0:0:0

Thrid line: FromOffsetX:FromOffsetY:FromOffsetZ:width:length:height.
Fourth line: ToOffsetX:ToOffsetY:ToOffsetZ


SWITCH
[RC1002]
0:1:0:1:1:1
0:0:0

Thrid line: FromOffsetX:FromOffsetY:FromOffsetZ:width:length:height.
Fourth line: ToOffsetX:ToOffsetY:ToOffsetZ


RANDOM
[RC1003]
0:1:0:1:1:1
0

Thrid line: OffsetX:OffsetY:OffsetZ:width:length:height.
Fourth line: 0 for one solid random color or 1 for all blocks individual random color
